<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 4th year of Kōpparakesarivarman. For Mahādeva of Tiruvālantuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> in Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam (<foreign>kuṉṟakūttu</foreign> &gt; <foreign>kuṉṟakkūṟṟattu</foreign>), Nilaiyaṉ Vempaṉ, a shepherd <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>maṉṟāṭi</foreign></supplied> of this village <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivvūr</foreign></supplied>, to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> one sacred lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oru tiruviḷakku</foreign></supplied> as long as the sun and the moon endure (<foreign>candrādityal</foreign> &gt; <foreign>candrādityaval</foreign>), for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neykku</foreign></supplied> by the <foreign>nārāyam</foreign> [measure] every day (<foreign>nicata </foreign>&gt; <foreign>nicatam</foreign>), gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 90 undying and non-ageing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvā</foreign></supplied> great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perāṭu</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p></div>

